N2  - Background: According literature, most fetal defects are associated with genetic and environmental causes, among them, exposure of pregnant women to pesticides [1]. There are few references about ingestion of pesticides and their consequences in neonates, in this case by oral ingestion by mothers during pregnancy for suicide purpose. In this country, pesticides are available, not under control and of easy access and low cost. Objective: To study occurrence of neonatal malformations after suicide attempt with pesticides in pregnant women, by oral ingestión mostly of rodenticide poisons, trying to identify the period of toxic ingestión by trimesters. Method: Descriptive and retrospective trial, with evaluation of pregnant women, revision of Clinical Histories, Suicide Intention Scale application, Intervention of Team forf Suicide Prevention, and appropiate Statistical Analysis, in those who had been attempted suicide by pesticides, assessed in an Emergency Room of a Mental Health Institution: this kind of events occurred in case of emotional crises, anxious or severe depressive states, generally through conjugal conflicts, but also in any other clinical complications. The study included further gynecologic, Pediatric and Genetical examination of mothers and babies respectively, excluding those without familial antecedents of neonatal malformations, along a decade. Most of patients had been referred from a General Hospital after being in Unit of Critical Care for an acute treatment and antidote application. Results: They were evaluated 7350 pregnant women who attempted suicide by diverse methods, 2940 of them (40 %) had been used pesticides. We found in 8 suicidal attempters (0.27 %) neonates with malformations: in 2 babies:Hydrocephalia, in other 2:cardiovascular malformations, in 2 gastrointestinal malformations, in 1: leap malformations, and in other 1: sindactilia. All suicide attempts had been occurred in first trimester of Pregnancy, and patients expressed several motivations, especially conjugal conflicts generally with opposition of pregnancy state of pair. Age ranked between 19 and 44 years old. Clinical diagnoses were: Major Depressive Disorder: 4 pregnants, Bipolar Disorder: 3 of them, and Schizophrenic Disorder: 1 of them. Conclusion: According this trial, neonatal malformations of suicide attempt pregnants using pesticides, mostly of easy availability, during first trimester of pregnancy, with stressor of extreme conjugal problems, generally by opposition of pregnancy of pair, without these antecedents in relatives, could be the consequence of this kind of toxics, and seems to be low, although there were founded compromise in several neonate organs. It could not be posible to identify toxicity level in all cases; but this kind of consequence becomes an additional risk factor for mothers, increasing suicidal behavior potential. Authors recommend to follow World Helath Organization´s advises about restriction of accessibility to pesticides in general, and have a better care of Prenatal Control in mothers confronting the described happening.
