N2  - Hipochondroplasia is an osteochondrodyplasia characterized by short stature. Clinical and molecularly similar to achondroplasia since the shortening of legs and bowing of the extremities occur in both syndromes The causative mutations of both entities are in the FGFR3 gene. Misdiagnosis is common since clinical manifestations are subtle in hypochondroplasia. The knowledge, identification and genetic assessment are necessary to avoid possible complications and to evaluate orthopedic therapy with leg lengthening combined with correction of bowlegs as an alternative until we have something else to offer to these patients.
