N2  - In this double-blind study we compared alprazolam, clobazam, and placebo for the treatment of outpatients suffering from generalized anxiety disorder. At the end of the treatment, the three groups were significantly improved without showing differences among them. However, both active-drug groups were much improved at the end ot week 1 in contrast to the placebo group. We were unable to find any difference on efficacy evaluations between alprazolam and clobazam, but alprazolam reached a consistently better outcome on some ratings compared to placebo. Although benzodiazepines share many common properties, it is necessary to identify selected groups of patients that can be helped by specific compounds or even placebo.
