N2  - Cultures of B. bacilliformis require growth factors which are found in the erythrocytes. The use of a 2 layered medium (gel phase) and a gel plasma medium (simple gel) indicated that these factors are not present in plasma, stroma or leukocytes. The usual bacteriologic media are ineffective for securing growth, but with the addition of a small amount of blood agar the bacteria develop.
