N2  - Erythrocytic factor required by B. bacilliformis was found in mammalian red blood cells and avian erythrocytes, but was not found in blood plasma. However, guinea pig plasma supported the growth of B. bacilliformis. The erythrocytic factor diffuses easily from the red blood cell to plasma, agar, gel and saline solutions. The factor is resistant to heat and weak acids.
